msgctxt "Talk11"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Hm? Your pouch is...glowing? <2.te_si><3.pa><4.te_si>Could it\n"
"be you brought me some <5.se_co>fireflies<6.re_co>?<7.te_si>\n"
"\n"
"<8.so>I'm actually crazy busy right now...<9.pa>\n"
"Maybe you could come by my house later?<10.te_si>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (longer)
msgctxt "Talk12"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Huh? That glowing... <2.pa>Could it be you\n"
"caught some?! Show me, show me!"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: set_colour (red)
#. 3: reset_colour
#. 4: sound
#. 5: set_colour (red)
#. 6: reset_colour
msgctxt "Talk13"
msgid ""
"<1.so>*sigh*\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"They say the roads are dangerous at\n"
"night, so I have to come straight home\n"
"without searching for <2.se_co>fireflies<3.re_co>...\n"
"I miss them so much. And the night sky...\n"
"Now it's the same tired thing every night.\n"
"I'm so sick of it...\n"
"<4.so>If only the <5.se_co>fireflies <6.re_co>would come to play\n"
"here so I could still see them..."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: choice
msgctxt "Talk14"
msgid ""
"<1.so>They glow so prettily...\n"
"It's magical...<2.ch>"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (longer)
msgctxt "Talk17"
msgid "<1.so>Heehee! <2.pa>Thanks!"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: pause (longer)
msgctxt "Talk18"
msgid "<1.so>Ugh! <2.pa>Boys are SO unromantic..."
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
msgctxt "Talk20"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Thank you... This is all I have to offer,\n"
"but please accept it with my gratitude!"
msgstr ""

